&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve seen a few tricks for getting what Apple calls the Marketing Model name of a Mac in Terminal. One uses the last 4 characters of the serial number in a &lt;code&gt;curl&lt;/code&gt; command. This seems to work (it requires the &lt;code&gt;-L&lt;/code&gt; flag on &lt;code&gt;curl&lt;/code&gt;). It may stop working because of changes to Apple serial numbers.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>